				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not sure if you are aware... that or this is only something that my brain dead pet does........
<br />

<br />
There seems to be a slight difference between /pet hold, and /pet back off.
<br />
/pet Hold 
<br />
Will make your pet stop attacking , and make him not attack until told to do so...... downside he will go RIGHT back to attacking whatever mob he last was attacking.... no matter how many times you yell F'ing Pet at your pc and hammer at key board /pet attack /pet hold /pet attack /pet hold /pet attack. Your pet WILL ignore you and attack the last mob he got a taste for. Of course this does not hold true for low hp aggro (which is when a npc/pet will turn and attack anything that is under ~8% life).
<br />

<br />
/pet back off
<br />
Seems to have a minor aggro wipe effect to it. As long as you or your pet are not hit again before you give the /pet attack command, your pet will listen and attack the mob you tell him too, and generally stick on it. Unless another mob starts whacking on your pet, or low hp aggro kicks in.
<br />

<br />
